---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MarketStructureLine from '../components/MarketStructureLine.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="The story behind Garden and my journey into trading and systems.">
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif mb-6">About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose text-text-secondary">
      <p>
        I started <strong>Garden</strong> because I realized that my best learning happened when I was forced to explain my thoughts to someone else. Trading is a solitary pursuit, and it's easy to get lost in your own biases if you don't have a way to externalize your process.
      </p>

      <p>
        This is not a site for signals or "get rich quick" schemes. It's a documentation of a long-term journey. I am a trader, but I am also a developer and a builder. I believe that the same principles of discipline, iteration, and systems thinking apply across all these domains.
      </p>

      <h2>The Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        The name "Garden" comes from the idea that a trading career is something you cultivate. You don't "conquer" the market; you learn to exist within it, much like a gardener works with the land. You prepare your mind, you follow your rules, and you accept what the market gives you.
      </p>

      <p>
        I value simplicity over complexity. I value the process over the outcome. And I value consistency over luck.
      </p>

      <h2>The Goal</h2>
      <p>
        My goal is to reach a level of mastery where the execution of my system is as natural as breathing. This site is my record of that pursuit—the successes, the failures, and the lessons learned along the way.
      </p>

      <MarketStructureLine variant="divider" class="h-4 w-full my-12 opacity-30" />

      <p class="text-sm font-sans text-text-tertiary lowercase">
        if you want to get in touch, i'm probably somewhere watching a 15m chart.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
